There's a lot here. Some is good print quality, some not. In some cases it's not good enough legibility to read but may be useful for reference if you don't mind straining your eyes a bit. I suppose it has archival value too because many of these books may never be available in hardcopy print again. There's also a lot that is NOT here, of importance, so this isn't a panacea for chess book lovers - just another possible alternate source.
